-- Ecobank says IFC to swap $75 mln debt into equity on July 1
-- By Chijioke Ohuocha
-- Sat Jun 14, 2014 04:06PM EDT
-- None



ABUJA, June 14 (Reuters) - Pan-African lender Ecobank <ETI.LG> <EGB.GH> said the International Finance Corporation (IFC) would swap $75.2 million worth of its convertible debt into equity on July 1, increasing Ecobank's total shares outstanding by 5 percent.

Ecobank said in a regulatory statement late on Friday it would issue 838.3 million shares to two funds managed by the World Bank's IFC unit, increasing its total shares to 18.1 billion.